1
00:00:07,433 --> 00:00:09,833
It writes about love in such a deep way.

2
00:00:10,166 --> 00:00:12,800
This book made me cry. Thank you so much.

3
00:00:13,933 --> 00:00:17,066
Every rule feels like a moment I've lived through.

4
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:21,400
It completely changed how I see relationships.

5
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:23,966
I saw myself in every line.

6
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:26,533
10 Rules Before I Fell for You

7
00:00:26,766 --> 00:00:30,600
is a book everyone should read at least once in their life.

8
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:46,533
Of course I understand it,

9
00:00:46,966 --> 00:00:48,566
otherwise how could I write something like this?

10
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:56,166
Thank you for writing such a wonderful book for us.

11
00:00:58,300 --> 00:01:01,285
There are so many positive comments.

12
00:01:01,816 --> 00:01:04,200
I don't have to care that one meaningless comment.

13
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:16,433
It's as bitter as that comment.

14
00:01:22,444 --> 00:01:26,700
Do you know how many months of research I do?

15
00:01:27,033 --> 00:01:28,733
How many psychology books I read?

16
00:01:28,766 --> 00:01:30,100
How many drafts I wrote?

17
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,600
And who is this "LeanNote"?

18
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:34,800
You really had fun doing that?

19
00:01:35,912 --> 00:01:42,817
Ten rules, huh? Written like someone who knows love but actually doesn't understand it at all.

20
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:49,966
It's just one negative comment, I don't care.

21
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:05,133
Or maybe they're right.

22
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,566
No,

23
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:15,766
love has reasons, evidences, theories, and equations.

24
00:02:21,966 --> 00:02:22,800
Okay,

25
00:02:23,066 --> 00:02:28,433
then I'll show you how people who understand love write about it.

26
00:03:00,978 --> 00:03:05,000
Hello, Ms. Ticha, are you the one who booked the long-term accommodation?

27
00:03:05,622 --> 00:03:06,338
Hello.

28
00:03:07,066 --> 00:03:07,566
Yes, it's me.

29
00:03:08,447 --> 00:03:09,698
I'm Lean.

30
00:03:10,057 --> 00:03:12,057
This is a forest garden house surrounded by mountains,

31
00:03:12,262 --> 00:03:13,659
a little distance from Bangkok,

32
00:03:13,728 --> 00:03:15,364
but very peaceful.

33
00:03:17,069 --> 00:03:19,851
It is so quiet, isn't it?

34
00:03:20,538 --> 00:03:23,380
Great, I can concentrate on my work.

35
00:03:23,862 --> 00:03:25,133
Then you've come to the right place,

36
00:03:25,387 --> 00:03:28,592
because the only noise here is the sound of crickets chirping

37
00:03:28,592 --> 00:03:30,592
or dogs barking.

38
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,086
Sounds great.

39
00:03:34,439 --> 00:03:36,460
You must be tired, go rest first.

40
00:03:36,657 --> 00:03:38,349
I'll take you to your room.

41
00:03:39,550 --> 00:03:42,727
Thank you. I'm really grateful for your help.

42
00:04:09,303 --> 00:04:12,400
If you need anything else, please feel free to call me anytime.

43
00:04:12,557 --> 00:04:14,776
because we're a small family here.

44
00:04:15,811 --> 00:04:16,758
Thank you.

45
00:04:17,820 --> 00:04:20,740
What a great weather.

46
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:24,136
It feels like time is slowing down.

47
00:04:24,711 --> 00:04:25,340
Yes, that's right.

48
00:04:26,059 --> 00:04:29,194
When you're here, you have to let time slow down a bit,

49
00:04:29,475 --> 00:04:31,896
because you'll miss out on the peace and quiet times.

50
00:04:32,928 --> 00:04:38,020
You sound like someone who's been through a lot!.

51
00:04:39,383 --> 00:04:40,180
No, not really.

52
00:04:40,536 --> 00:04:43,620
I've just seen people try to escape the hustle and bustle,

53
00:04:43,719 --> 00:04:45,719
but end up bringing it along anyway.

54
00:04:49,170 --> 00:04:49,780
By the way,

55
00:04:50,014 --> 00:04:52,729
I think I saw you mentioned in your booking that

56
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,289
you work online?

57
00:04:55,225 --> 00:04:58,781
If it's not too much of a secret, may I ask what you do?

58
00:04:59,930 --> 00:05:01,340
It's not a secret at all,

59
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:04,464
I'm a book writer.

60
00:05:05,348 --> 00:05:06,300
Really?

61
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:09,491
I love reading books,

62
00:05:10,001 --> 00:05:13,164
but lately I haven't been reading much.

63
00:05:13,492 --> 00:05:14,140
Really?

64
00:05:14,622 --> 00:05:15,361
What...

65
00:05:15,694 --> 00:05:17,694
kind of books do you read?

66
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:23,462
The kind that doesn't teach anyone how to love.

67
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:34,240
Maybe they didn't intend to teach anyone anything.

68
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:41,380
They just want people to understand each other better,

69
00:05:42,882 --> 00:05:45,443
including themselves, perhaps.

70
00:05:46,756 --> 00:05:47,256
Yeah?

71
00:05:47,495 --> 00:05:50,000
But trying too hard to understand

72
00:05:50,084 --> 00:05:53,051
might make us forget our true feelings.

73
00:05:56,944 --> 00:05:58,608
Do you want to rest?

74
00:05:58,972 --> 00:06:00,943
There's a traditional Thai dinner in the garden, waiting for you.

75
00:06:01,265 --> 00:06:04,618
if you want a peaceful and delicious experience, don't forget to come.

76
00:06:06,725 --> 00:06:07,632
Thank you.

77
00:07:16,713 --> 00:07:18,540
The writing is beautiful.

78
00:07:18,686 --> 00:07:20,490
It made me miss my lover.

79
00:07:20,854 --> 00:07:24,466
A book that helped me understand love from a new perspective.

80
00:07:24,805 --> 00:07:26,805
Please write the next book soon.

81
00:07:41,220 --> 00:07:43,302
Afraid to admit your feelings - LeanNote

82
00:07:43,302 --> 00:07:44,980
Another problematic comment.

83
00:07:46,043 --> 00:07:48,744
I told you the author must understand,

84
00:07:48,984 --> 00:07:50,465
otherwise how could they write it?

85
00:07:52,554 --> 00:07:54,218
Do you know better than me or what?

86
00:07:54,565 --> 00:07:58,261
My book is a bestseller!

87
00:08:07,593 --> 00:08:10,760
I guess it's because of that problematic commenter that

88
00:08:11,325 --> 00:08:14,544
I can't write my new book.

89
00:08:25,441 --> 00:08:26,867
It's as bitter as the criticism.

90
00:09:11,731 --> 00:09:13,433
Why didn't they respond me at all?

91
00:09:13,775 --> 00:09:15,000
You're not really that tough, are you?

92
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:20,000
Don't get cocky.

93
00:09:26,315 --> 00:09:29,120
You probably don't have anyone and you're probably not good-looking either,

94
00:09:29,535 --> 00:09:30,974
that's why you don't reveal your identity.

95
00:09:38,257 --> 00:09:39,420
What evidence do you have

96
00:09:39,746 --> 00:09:43,274
that those ten ridiculous theories about falling in love

97
00:09:43,344 --> 00:09:44,573
are actually true?

98
00:09:53,653 --> 00:09:56,420
Are you Leannote?

99
00:10:17,441 --> 00:10:22,500
Don't tell me that it is your book.

100
00:10:24,032 --> 00:10:28,532
I'm the one you've been insulting for five minutes straight.

101
00:10:31,207 --> 00:10:32,614
What a small world.

102
00:10:33,974 --> 00:10:36,480
Maybe it's because some people just

103
00:10:36,751 --> 00:10:39,256
like to stay in their own little world.

104
00:10:40,153 --> 00:10:43,440
Those who wrote theories about how to start liking someone

105
00:10:43,889 --> 00:10:46,433
are probably living in their own world too, right?

106
00:10:47,134 --> 00:10:48,000
At least...

107
00:10:48,408 --> 00:10:51,459
I'm not coward to express it, unlike some people...

108
00:10:51,797 --> 00:10:53,321
Those who like to hide behind keyboards.

109
00:10:53,968 --> 00:10:55,480
Maybe...

110
00:10:56,336 --> 00:10:58,280
the person who wrote it just felt

111
00:10:58,364 --> 00:11:01,359
scared and wrote it to convince themselves.

112
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:13,240
I'll use those ten rules

113
00:11:14,116 --> 00:11:15,373
with you.

114
00:11:16,239 --> 00:11:18,954
And you'll find out on yourself whether this theory is

115
00:11:19,269 --> 00:11:20,050
true...

116
00:11:20,565 --> 00:11:22,565
or just crazy as you said.

117
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:25,940
You don't want to prove any theory,

118
00:11:26,515 --> 00:11:29,234
You just want to conquer other people's feelings.

119
00:11:31,243 --> 00:11:32,598
And if I actually win,

120
00:11:33,243 --> 00:11:34,700
will you still dare to stand here?

121
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:38,520
Let's see

122
00:11:39,547 --> 00:11:41,141
if the person who wrote the theories

123
00:11:41,792 --> 00:11:43,792
can actually put it into practice.

124
00:11:52,491 --> 00:11:53,954
Then you'll know for yourself

125
00:11:54,173 --> 00:11:57,715
that this theory isn't as crazy as you say.

126
00:11:58,201 --> 00:11:59,488
So, go ahead..

127
00:12:00,313 --> 00:12:02,972
And if your theory is true,

128
00:12:03,132 --> 00:12:04,670
I'll accept it.

129
00:12:06,468 --> 00:12:07,495
Saying that...

130
00:12:08,341 --> 00:12:10,367
means okay, right?

131
00:12:11,811 --> 00:12:14,353
It means I'm not a coward.

